gomodel:SYNGO_5194  a    owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment     "Rationale: Figure 4c, S7, S7: pulldown of endogenous RPS23RG1 in wildtype and RPS23RG1-knockout mice showed interaction with PSD93 (DLG2) and PSD95 (DLG4).\n\nFigure 4d: confocal imaging of overexpressed human HA-tagged RPS23RG1 in mouse primary neuronal cultures showed partial co-localization with PSD93 (DLG2) and PSD95 (DLG4).\n\nFurther, authors showed RPS23RG1 enhanced PSD93 and PSD95 turnover (Fig. 3, 4).. Experimental description: annotated the confocal localization evidence in Figure 4d; \"HA-tagged human RR1 was transfected into WT mouse primary neurons at DIV4.\"\n\nthe human protein sequence is described in PMID:26733416 and is available as GenBank nucleotide ID MH807581.1" ;
        lego:modelstate  "production" ;
        dc:contributor   "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date          "2023-03-27" ;
        dc:title         "SYNGO_CC_5194" ;
        pav:providedBy   "https://syngo.vu.nl" .

